dfischer.utils

Class DataCollectionSequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.DataCollectionSequence

  • public class DataCollectionSequence
extends java.lang.Object
    Contain a sequence of measured data items and their time stamps which are dynamically measured on the fly during load test execution. Data collection sequences can be added at runtime during load test execution. All items that are added to the sequence should be of the same item type, except error event items which can combined with any other item type into the same sequence.
    See Also:
    DataCollectionFloatItem, DataCollectionYZFloatItem, DataCollectionTextItem, DataCollectionErrorEventItem

      static int CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE
      Cluster option for DataCollectionFloatItem(s): Unite the (same) data collection sequence of all cluster members to a single data collection sequence, which contains the mathematical average of all member sequences.
      static int CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE_LASTVALID
      Cluster option for DataCollectionFloatItem(s): performs the same algorithm as described for the cluster option CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE, but uses - if no further data of a cluster member are available - the last valid data of the cluster member (instead of zero values).
      static int CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM
      Cluster option for DataCollectionFloatItem(s): Unite the (same) data collection sequence of all cluster members to a single data collection sequence, which contains the mathematical sum of all member sequences.
      static int CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM_LASTVALID
      Cluster option for DataCollectionFloatItem(s): performs the same algorithm as described for the cluster option CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM, but uses - if no further data of a cluster member are available - the last valid data of the cluster member (instead of zero values).

    • Field Detail

      • CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM

        public static final int CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM
        Cluster option for DataCollectionFloatItem(s): Unite the (same) data collection sequence of all cluster members to a single data collection sequence, which contains the mathematical sum of all member sequences.
        Note: this cluster option cannot be combined with the options CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM_LASTVALID, CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE or CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE_LASTVALID.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM_LASTVALID

        public static final int CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM_LASTVALID
        Cluster option for DataCollectionFloatItem(s): performs the same algorithm as described for the cluster option CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM, but uses - if no further data of a cluster member are available - the last valid data of the cluster member (instead of zero values).
        Note: this cluster option cannot be combined with the options CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM, CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE or CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE_LASTVALID.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE

        public static final int CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE
        Cluster option for DataCollectionFloatItem(s): Unite the (same) data collection sequence of all cluster members to a single data collection sequence, which contains the mathematical average of all member sequences.
        Note: this cluster option cannot be combined with the options CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM, CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM_LASTVALID or CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE_LASTVALID.

    • Method Detail

      • setItemType

        public void setItemType(int itemType)
        Set the data item type of the sequence. This can be either ITEM_TYPE_FLOAT_VALUE, or ITEM_TYPE_YZ_FLOAT_VALUE, or ITEM_TYPE_TEXT_FRAGMENT. It's recommended to call this method just after creating a new instance in order to give the GUI a hint about visualizing the data in case of an empty sequence or in case when the sequence contains only error events.
        Note that the item type cannot be changed once its set and and also cannot be changed after adding items to the sequence.
        Parameters:
        itemType - the data item type of the sequence
        Since:
        V5.5-D
        See Also:
        DataCollectionAbstractItem.ITEM_TYPE_FLOAT_VALUE, DataCollectionAbstractItem.ITEM_TYPE_YZ_FLOAT_VALUE, DataCollectionAbstractItem.ITEM_TYPE_TEXT_FRAGMENT

      • addClusterOption

        public void addClusterOption(int clusterOption,
                    java.lang.String diagramSubTitle)
        Allows to set one or several options about how the data are merged when a load generating cluster is used.
        You can call this method several times to set several, different options.
        Note: if no option is set, the data are not merged.
        Parameters:
        clusterOption - the option about how to merge the data when a load generating cluster is used.
        diagramSubTitle - the new diagram sub title for the merged data, or null if no new diagram sub title is required.
        See Also:
        CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM, CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_SUM_LASTVALID, CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE, CLUSTER_OPTION_MERGE_FLOAT_ITEMS_TO_AVERAGE_LASTVALID

      • getClusterOptions

        public int getItemType()
        Return the data item type of the sequence. Note that ITEM_TYPE_ERROR_EVENT can be mixed into the same sequence with any other data item type. Therefore this method never return as result ITEM_TYPE_ERROR_EVENT.
